<!DOCTYPE ui:UiBinder SYSTEM "http://dl.google.com/gwt/DTD/xhtml.ent">
<ui:UiBinder xmlns:ui="urn:ui:com.google.gwt.uibinder"
        xmlns:g="urn:import:com.google.gwt.user.client.ui">

    <ui:with field="res" type="com.arcbees.website.client.resources.AppResources"/>
    <ui:with field="page" type="com.arcbees.website.client.resources.PageProductResources"/>
    <ui:with field="fonts" type="com.arcbees.website.client.resources.FontResources"/>

    <g:HTMLPanel styleName="{page.style.products} {page.style.gwtp}">

        <nav class="{page.style.breadcrumb}">
            <span class="{fonts.icons.iconArcbees} {page.style.logo}"></span>
            <ul>
                <li>PRODUCT</li>
                <li>GWTP</li>
            </ul>
        </nav>

        <section class="{res.style.stripe}">
            <div class="{res.grid.row} {res.style.clearfix} {res.style.wrapper}">
                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_1_2}">
                    <h1>gwt platform
                        <a href="#" class="{res.style.anchor}">#</a>
                    </h1>
                    <h2 class="{page.style.presentation}">The best Model View
                        <span>Presenter framework</span>
                        for GWT
                    </h2>
                    <div class="{page.style.socialTop}">
                        <ul class="{page.style.social}">
                            <li>
                                <a href="#" class="{fonts.icons.iconGPlus}">
                                    <span class="{res.style.hidden}">Google plus</span>
                                </a>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <a href="#" class="{fonts.icons.iconGitHub}">
                                    <span class="{res.style.hidden}">Github</span>
                                </a>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_push_1_2} {res.grid.col_m_full} {res.grid.col_m_push_0}">
                    <p>
                        <strong>GWT-Platform (GWTP) is your best friend for building large Google Web Toolkit (GWT) web
                            apps.
                        </strong>
                    </p>
                    <p>Used by hundreds of teams around the world, GWTP will help you push your GWT app to the next
                        level!
                    </p>
                    <p>Combining powerful features, GWTP is an out-of-the-box solution that supports all the
                        requirements of modern web apps.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="{page.style.slideshow} {res.style.wrapper}">
                <div class="{page.style.slides}">
                    <g:Image resource="{page.gwtpScreen1}"/>
                </div>
                <a href="#" class="{page.style.prev}">
                    <span class="{res.style.hidden}">Prev</span>
                </a>
                <a href="#" class="{page.style.next}">
                    <span class="{res.style.hidden}">Next</span>
                </a>
                <nav class="{page.style.pager} {res.style.centered}">
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <a href="#"></a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="#"></a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="#"></a>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </nav>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="{res.style.stripe} {page.style.stripeDetails} {res.style.centered}">
            <h2>in details</h2>
        </section>

        <section class="{res.style.stripe} {page.style.stripeDetails} {res.style.medium1}">
            <div class="{res.grid.row} {res.style.clearfix} {res.style.wrapper}">

                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_1_3}">
                    <h3>Model View Presenter Framework</h3>
                    <a href="#" class="{res.style.anchor}">#</a>
                </div>

                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_2_3}">
                    <p>Web applications need a solid underlying architecture to build upon as they grow. GWTP’s MVP
                        framework helps you organize your code for scalability right from the start, with a clear
                        separation of concerns between your UI and your business logic.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="{res.style.stripe} {page.style.stripeDetails} {res.style.medium2}">
            <div class="{res.grid.row} {res.style.clearfix} {res.style.wrapper}">

                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_1_3}">
                    <h3>dependency injection</h3>
                    <a href="#" class="{res.style.anchor}">#</a>
                </div>

                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_2_3}">
                    <p>GWTP was engineered with dependency injection in mind. Leveraging the full power of Google Gin
                        and Guice, GWTP makes your web apps more modular and testable.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="{res.style.stripe} {page.style.stripeDetails} {res.style.medium3}">
            <div class="{res.grid.row} {res.style.clearfix} {res.style.wrapper}">

                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_1_3}">
                    <h3>history management</h3>
                    <a href="#" class="{res.style.anchor}">#</a>
                </div>

                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_2_3}">
                    <p>GWTP's PlaceManager makes it trivial to build a blazing fast modern web app that minimizes
                        client-server roundtrips while making sure the Back button works as users expect.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="{res.style.stripe} {page.style.stripeDetails}">
            <div class="{res.grid.row} {res.style.clearfix} {res.style.wrapper}">

                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_1_3}">
                    <h3>command pattern</h3>
                    <a href="#" class="{res.style.anchor}">#</a>
                </div>

                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_2_3}">
                    <p>Client/Server communication is made easy using GWTP's integrated command pattern. With it, you
                        can easily create Actions that are managed by server-side Handlers. Also included: asynchronous
                        callbacks and server-side Handler protection.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="{res.style.stripe} {page.style.stripeDetails} {res.style.medium1}">
            <div class="{res.grid.row} {res.style.clearfix} {res.style.wrapper}">

                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_1_3}">
                    <h3>code splitting</h3>
                    <a href="#" class="{res.style.anchor}">#</a>
                </div>

                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_2_3}">
                    <p>Javascript-heavy web applications can take too long to download as your application grows in
                        size. Thankfully, GWTP comes with effortless and efficient code splitting that will cut through
                        your application's startup time.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="{res.style.stripe} {page.style.stripeDetails} {res.style.medium2}">
            <div class="{res.grid.row} {res.style.clearfix} {res.style.wrapper}">

                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_1_3}">
                    <h3>mobile ready</h3>
                    <a href="#" class="{res.style.anchor}">#</a>
                </div>

                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_2_3}">
                    <p>GWTP allows you to easily create multiple instances of a Presenter. This lets you reuse the same
                        widgets and logic throughout your application without duplicating your code.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="{res.style.stripe} {page.style.stripeDetails} {res.style.medium3}">
            <div class="{res.grid.row} {res.style.clearfix} {res.style.wrapper}">

                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_1_3}">
                    <h3>Nested Presenters</h3>
                    <a href="#" class="{res.style.anchor}">#</a>
                </div>

                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_2_3}">
                    <p>Web apps usually require a consistent layout across all your pages. The last thing you want to do
                        is replicate your website header code on every page! GWTP solves that problem using Nested
                        Presenters, which are loosely coupled and communicate via a shared Event Bus.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="{page.style.moreFeatures} {res.style.stripe}">
            <div class="{res.grid.row} {res.style.clearfix} {res.style.wrapper}">
                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_full} {res.style.centered}">
                    <h2>more features
                        <a href="#" class="{res.style.anchor}">#</a>
                    </h2>
                </div>

                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_1_2} {res.grid.col_m_full}">
                    <h3>security</h3>
                    <p>GWTP allows you to protect your server using Action validation. In addition, you can block
                        specific pages using custom Gatekeepers. Also included: Automatic XSRF attack detection.
                    </p>
                    <h3>google analytics</h3>
                    <p>With as little as 3 lines of code, your web application will be integrated with Google Analytics.
                        Also, GWTP allows your website to be easily crawlable by search engines that follow Google's
                        AJAX Crawling specification.
                    </p>
                    <h3>Tabbed Presenters</h3>
                    <p>Often times you'll want to display a list of links that cause a child Presenter to appear. GWTP
                        makes it easy to create loosely-coupled Tabbed Presenters that live within their parent
                        Presenter.
                    </p>
                    <h3>maven</h3>
                    <p>If your project uses Maven, you're all set for GWTP. All the dependencies that you need to
                        migrate your project to GWTP are published to Maven Central. So, a couple lines in your POM, and
                        GWTP is ready!
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_1_2} {res.grid.col_m_full}">
                    <h3>Internationalization</h3>
                    <p>GWTP makes i18n easy. Using a custom Python script, GWTP will store all your translations in
                        separate properties files for all languages.
                    </p>
                    <h3>Crawlability</h3>
                    <p>Wondering if it's possible to make crawlable applications with GWTP? Absolutely! GWTP includes a
                        crawling engine that lets you make any of your asynchronous web sites crawlable - even if you're
                        not building them in GWTP!
                    </p>
                    <h3>Testability</h3>
                    <p>Because GWTP implements the Model View Presenter design pattern, most of your app logic will be
                        found inside the Presenters, which can be easily tested using Junit, Mockito and Jukito.
                    </p>
                    <h3>Route-like NameTokens</h3>
                    <p>Want human-readable URLs? With GWTP, your URLs can look like REST calls! Using Route-Like
                        NameTokens, fussy web addresses like /#userprofile?id=999 can be replaced with
                        /#/userprofile/999. It’s a format your users will be able to recognize, remember and share.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="{res.style.stripe} {res.style.dark} {res.style.centered}">
            <div class="{res.grid.row} {res.style.clearfix} {res.style.wrapper}">
                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_full}">

                    <h3>ALL THE DOCUMENTATIONS
                        <span>YOU NEED</span>
                    </h3>
                    <a href="#" class="{res.style.btn}">Go to Arcbees Developers</a>

                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="{res.style.stripe} {page.style.colored} {res.style.centered}">
            <div class="{res.grid.row} {res.style.clearfix} {res.style.wrapper}">
                <div class="{res.grid.col} {res.grid.col_full}">

                    <h3>SHARE</h3>
                    <ul class="{page.style.social}">
                        <li>
                            <a href="#" class="{fonts.icons.iconFb}">
                                <span class="{res.style.hidden}">Facebook</span>
                            </a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="#" class="{fonts.icons.iconTwitter}">
                                <span class="{res.style.hidden}">Twitter</span>
                            </a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="#" class="{fonts.icons.iconGPlus}">
                                <span class="{res.style.hidden}">Google</span>
                            </a>
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

    </g:HTMLPanel>
</ui:UiBinder>
